Global install (recommended)npx (no install)Project-local (CI/CD) <pre><code>npm install -g @doquflow/cli
</code></pre> <p>Installs the <code>docuflow</code> command globally. Run it from any project directory.</p> <pre><code>docuflow --version   # verify install
docuflow --help      # see all commands
</code></pre> <pre><code>npx @doquflow/cli init
</code></pre> <p>Runs the latest version without a permanent install. Best for one-off initialisation.</p> <pre><code>npm install --save-dev @doquflow/cli
</code></pre> <p>Then call via <code>npx docuflow</code> or add to your <code>package.json</code> scripts:</p> <pre><code>{
  "scripts": {
    "docuflow:sync": "docuflow sync --ai"
  }
}
</code></pre>
